# city-connect-service
This is web service which determines if two cities are connected. Two cities are considered connected 
if there’s a series of roads that can be traveled from one city to another. 
Any unexpected input should result in a ’no’ response

Requirements:
  Requires Maven 3 or newer and Java JDK 8 or newer.

To build the jar:
  mvn clean install

To run tests and coverage report:
  mvn clean verify


To run:
  java -jar city-connect-service-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar.

URL format:
    http://localhost:8080/connected?origin=city1&destination=city2

Example usage:
    > curl http://localhost:8080/connected?origin=Boston&destination=Newark
    Yes

    > curl http://localhost:8080/connected?origin=Philadelphia&destination=Albany
    No
	
To see api documentation:
	http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
